BuildRequires:    R-survival 
Requires:         R-survival 

%description
Estimates the log hazard ratio associated with a binary exposure using a
Cox PH model weighted by the propensity score. Propensity model is
estimated using a simple logistic regression. Variance estimation takes
into account the propensity score estimation step with the method proposed
by Hajage et al. (2018) <doi:10.1002/bimj.201700330>. Both the average
treatment effect on the overall (ATE) or the treated (ATT) population can
be estimated. For the ATE estimation, both unstabilized and stabilized
weights can be used.

